==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zion
<hw>Zi"on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>ts⟦imac⟧y⟦omac⟧n</ets>, originally, a hill.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Jewish Antiq.)</fld> <def>A hill in Jerusalem,
which, after the capture of that city by the Israelites, became the
royal residence of David and his successors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, the theocracy, or church of God.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The heavenly Jerusalem; heaven.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zionism</ent>⟦br⟧
